# Core Package Rules (element / math / common)

These packages are the foundation the whole app builds on. Changes here ripple everywhere.

- **Respect the dependency direction:** `element → math → common`. Never import "upward"
  (e.g. `math` must not import from `element`; nothing here imports from `@excalidraw/excalidraw`).
  If you reach for an upward import, the abstraction is in the wrong package — stop and flag it.
- **Keep `math` pure.** No DOM, no React, no side effects — deterministic functions only.
  This is what makes it unit-testable and reusable.
- **Element changes must preserve invariants:** binding (`boundElements`/`containerId`),
  z-index ordering, and version/versionNonce bumps. If you change an element's shape, update
  the corresponding transform + binding logic and add a regression test.
- **No breaking changes to exported types without a note** — these types are part of the
  public `@excalidraw/*` surface used by external integrators (VSCode, Obsidian, Notion).
- **Every behavioral change gets a Vitest test** co-located with the source.

Prefer adding a pure helper in `math`/`common` over inlining geometry in `element`.
